    "topic": "4. Root Word - Bene",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Bene → Good, Well (अच्छा, भला)",
        "content": "• MEANING:- good, well (Latin origin)\n• अर्थ:- अच्छा, भला (लैटिन)\n\n• EXAMPLES:-\n1. Benefit = bene (good) + fit (make/do) → something good (लाभ)\n2. Benevolent = bene (good) + vol (wish) → kind, well-wishing (दयालु)\n3. Benefactor = bene (good) + factor (doer) → one who does good (परोपकारी)\n4. Beneficial = bene (good) + ficial (making) → helpful, useful (लाभकारी)\n5. Benediction = bene (good) + diction (speak) → blessing (आशीर्वाद)\n\n• NOTE:- Words with 'bene' root always indicate goodness, kindness, or benefit."
